  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb2\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bc8 \u0b9a\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf \u0b9a\u0bc2\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bb2\u0bbf - \u0b92\u0bb0\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd 21 \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "One killed in Kolonnawa junction shooting - 21 killed in one month",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "A man has been shot dead in Kolonnawa this evening (30) amid a series of shootings in the country.",
        "Police spokesman Senior Superintendent of Police Nihal Taltuwa said a 38-year-old man was killed when two unidentified men on a motorcycle opened fire at a junction in Kolonnawa.",
        "The cause of the murder was not immediately known and Wellampitiya police have launched a special investigation.",
        "Meanwhile, 21 people (including today's incident) have been shot dead across the country in the past month. According to police, the figure has been revealed.",
        "These murders were reported in the one month period from last May 30 to today (30).",
        "On May 30, a former Army soldier was killed and another wounded in a shooting in front of a bus station on the outskirts of Bestian Mawatha.",
        "It is suspected that the shooting was aimed at a relative (nephew) of the person killed on the 3rd in Aluthgama and that the soldiers who were returning from a trial may have been the target of the shooting when the identity of the person changed. The relative is said to be a state witness in the case of heroin seized by the police narcotics unit and resold to drug traffickers.",
        "This was followed by a series of shootings in Panadura, Aluthgama, Ahangama, Tangalle, Wattala, Batticaloa, Kelaniya and Moratuwa.",
        "The country has been shocked by the recent spate of shootings targeting witnesses who provide information to the security forces on drug dealing.",
        "Intelligence has also been gathered that it is suspected that those involved in the drug trade and underworld activities who fled Sri Lanka to Dubai, India, France, Italy and the United Kingdom may have been involved in the killings.",
        "In this context, the special feature is that so far (this one month) the suspects (except for the Tangalle incident) who acted as unidentified gunmen who carried out such shootings have not been arrested."
      ],
